Clone the repository
Edit the docker-compose with the needed informations (Hostname, mail, volumes)
Run docker-compose up -d
Get a free SSL certificate from letsencrypt running the command:  docker exec -it nextcloud_core /certbot.sh
Adjust the DNS A record in order to point to your server
Go to: https://nextcloud.yourserver.com
Configure Nextcloud

- Optionally -
Remove the port 80 from docker-compose file, in order to take it accessible only via the 443 port

Enjoy!